Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Steam the sole for four minutes.Mix all the gremolata ingredients together in a bowl.Crush the tomatoes with one tablespoon of olive oil, the basil and the small bunch of flatleaf parsley. Season.Cut each fennel into 8 pieces and place in a roasting tray.  Pour over the wine, stock and dab on the butter. Place the fennel in the oven for 20 minutes.To serve, pile the tomatoes in the middle of a white plate. Pile  the steamed sole fillets on top, and spoon gremolata dressing over and around.  Serve with the braised fennel.